## Important rules

- **Use REAL vendor names, real diffs, real threat-model entries.** Generic training is what Hall is replacing.
- **The quiz IS the evidence.** No pass record → no compliance evidence. Score + sign + date.
- **Don't recycle last cycle's content verbatim.** SOC 2 asks for evidence of "ongoing" training; identical content year-over-year is a finding.
- **Founder is in scope.** SOC 2 CC1.4 covers "the entity." Hall takes the training and self-signs.
- **Contractors are in scope.** Anyone with prod access takes the training. Document it in the contract.
- **AI / LLM data handling is a 2026+ section.** Don't ship training without it if Hall uses any LLM in product or tooling.

## Disclaimer

**This skill is not a substitute for an enterprise security awareness platform
(KnowB4, Hoxhunt, Living Security, etc.) or qualified compliance counsel.**
/security-training generates project-specific content suitable for founder-mode
CISO operation; auditors will accept the material + signed records as evidence
for CC1.4 / A.6.3 / §164.308(a)(5) / Req 12.6, but as the team grows past ~10
people, a dedicated training platform with per-user tracking, regulatory updates,
and simulated phishing is the next step. For HIPAA + PHI scope, also engage a
qualified HIPAA security officer for content review. Always include this
disclaimer at the end of every report output.
